node.text:
How we grow and harvest our food is one of the biggest social and ecological cruces of our time. This Earth Day, we are proud to highlight that we use flour containing much or all of the original germ, oils and bran. Our flours are milled by our friends at @cairnspringmills in Skagit Valley; people we trust to take as much care with the milling and growing as we do with baking. 

Tartine and @cairnspringmills work with farmers like Dave Hedlin From @hedlinfamilyfarms to ensure that the grain being milled is not only sustainable but traceable.
